  "prompt": "What are the differences between RTGS and NEFT?",
  "response": "Here are the key differences between RTGS (Real-Time Gross Settlement) and NEFT (National Electronic Funds Transfer):\n\nRTGS:\n1. Instant real-time fund transfer\n2. Minimum transfer amount of \u20b92 lakh\n3. Funds transferred immediately\n4. Higher transaction charges\n5. Operates during banking hours\n6. Ideal for large value transactions\n7. Settlement happens on a transaction-by-transaction basis\n\nNEFT:\n1. Batch-based fund transfer\n2. No minimum transfer amount\n3. Transfers processed in batches (hourly)\n4. Lower transaction charges\n5. Operates during specific banking hours\n6. Suitable for smaller value transactions\n7. Net settlement at the end of the day\n\nCommon features:\n- Both are electronic fund transfer mechanisms\n- Operated by the Reserve Bank of India\n- Secure and reliable transfer methods\n- Available through bank branches and online banking\n- Transactions can be done 24/7 through internet banking\n\nEach method has its advantages, and the choice depends on the transaction amount, urgency, and cost considerations.",
